title: 56 Electronics Today International (ETI) Magazines.
description:
This is my personal collection of 56 ETI magazine scans, a great (the best IMO) UK-based electronics magazine that was published in the seventies to nineties era.  Also included is a Practical Electronics-sourced booklet for the 'Magnum' metal detector (which I built), and the source-code for a ETI project (which I also built!) and whose bug-laden firmware I also debugged & recompiled - of interest only to myself and the original author no doubt, but included here for completeness.  There's even the hard-to-read commented source-code for this included in the mix.

NOTE: This scans are NOT of high-quality!  My Canon scanner software is sh&t, allowing only 2 'quality' settings, the highest producing files almost 10 times the size.  So if this is a consideration, first download one or two issues and check them out before bitching about the quality.
